The United Nations Security Council has unanimously adopted UNSCR 2270, imposing significant sanctions on North Korea in response to its nuclear test and missile launch. The resolution aims to halt Pyongyang's weapons of mass destruction programs. The President welcomes this resolution as a united and appropriate response by the international community to North Korea's recent violations of Security Council resolutions. The international community has sent a clear message to North Korea that it must abandon these dangerous programs and choose a better path for its people.